Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Urban Corridor - High Street Policy Area

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE South Australian Metropolitan Investments is pleased to offer to the market, one of the best development sites of 2018. 

Located amongst the established high profile residential suburb of Prospect, 69-73 Prospect Road offers developers a corner site with substantial existing holding income. The property is in close proximity to infrastructure key to establishing the fantastic residential amenity that Prospect presents in the Palace Nova Cinemas directly adjacent, Coles Supermarket & cosmopolitan cafes and restaurants all within 500m walk.

CBRE further highlight the below development characteristics set to appeal to developers of all categories:

- Massive site area of 2,760sqm*
- Urban Corridor Zoning – High Street Policy Area
- Development up to 4 storeys permitted (STCC)
- Corner site with frontage of 53m* to Prospect Road
- Three existing certificates of title
- Fantastic residential amenity near Prospect Cinemas
- Gross holding income of $103,902.62pa* 
- Mixed use development site suited to high density residential, retail, commercial or aged care

For Sale by Expressions of Interest closing Thursday 6th September 2018 @ 4pm

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: SECURE LEASED INVESTMENT TO INTERNATIONAL BRAND

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
This well presented open-plan showroom is located on busy Main North Road, in a fantastic catchment located just 4 kilometres north of Adelaide’s CBD. This section of Main North Road is home to retailers such as Officeworks, 99 Bikes and Radio Rentals as well as many car dealerships.

The site has 46,800 vehicles passing the site per day, and offers multi- directional access from Gloucester Street, which is access via a rear lane way from the main car park. There are 13 car parks in the immediate car park, with an additional 4 car parks available in the adjacent car park.

According to the demographics analysis, there are just under 300,000 people living within a 10 minute drive time of the site. People living within the immediate 5 minute drive time catchment have a much higher than average household weekly income, earning $230 pw more than the average household in Adelaide. With more discretionary spend, they also spend more than the average household on food, clothing and household goods & furnishings.

The tenancy is in fantastic condition and is ready for immediate occupation.

*approx
